{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.303047+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "**Assignee:** Sean Bingham"}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.303047+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "---"}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.303047+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "### Root Cause"}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.305074+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "Salesforce's standard Case object does not record a timestamp when escalated. The `IsEscalated` field is boolean only — no timestamp data exists for elapsed-time reporting between Case open → escalation → close."}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.305586+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "---"}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.305586+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "### Solution"}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.307097+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "**Engineering escalation required.** Needs:"}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.307097+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "1. Custom field `Case.Escalation_DateTime__c` (Date/Time)"}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.309121+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "2. Record-Triggered Flow to stamp field on escalation"}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.309636+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "3. Salesforce report with elapsed-time formulas"}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.309636+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "**Critical blocker:** Escalation trigger mechanism must be confirmed with Noah Scott (checkbox toggle, Status change, queue reassignment, or Escalation Rule)."}
{"ts": "2026-05-16T23:33:06.311149+00:00", "run_key": "HEAL-33618", "kind": "line", "text": "---"}
